  "base_path": "/operator-licence-private-hire-vehicle",
  "content_id": "3b788418-e360-49d8-acf1-f1a0fa287b0c",
  "description": "Private hire vehicle operator licence; taxi, private hire, minicab, licence, vehicle.",
  "details": {
    "body": "<p>If you want to drive a private hire vehicle (<abbr title=\"Private Hire Vehicle\">PHV</abbr>) in England and Wales you need to either:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>get a <abbr title=\"Private Hire Vehicle\">PHV</abbr> operator licence yourself</li>\n  <li>drive a <abbr title=\"Private Hire Vehicle\">PHV</abbr> for a business which has a <abbr title=\"Private Hire Vehicle\">PHV</abbr> operator licence</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>A <abbr title=\"Private Hire Vehicle\">PHV</abbr> can only be pre-booked. Taxis can also be hired at a rank or hailed in the street.</p>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Information\" class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Taxis only need a taxi <a href=\"/taxi-vehicle-licence\">vehicle licence</a> and a taxi <a href=\"/taxi-driver-licence\">driver licence</a>. But taxi drivers can do work booked by an operator.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Private Hire Vehicle\">PHV</abbr> operator licences last for a maximum of 5 years.</p>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Warning\" class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You can be prosecuted if you receive payment for taking bookings or supply drivers for hire without an operator’s licence.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>There’s a different process for <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.nidirect.gov.uk/services/apply-taxi-operator-licence\">operator licences in Northern Ireland</a> and <a href=\"/find-licences/booking-office-licence-scotland\">booking office licences in Scotland</a>.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"apply\">Apply</h2>\n\n<p>Apply to the licensing authority where your <abbr title=\"Private Hire Vehicle\">PHV</abbr> business will operate. This is either:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>\n<a href=\"/find-your-local-council\">the local council</a> if you want to operate outside of London</li>\n  <li>\n<a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/info-for/taxis-and-private-hire/licensing/private-hire-operator-licence\">Transport for London (TfL) </a> if you want to operate in London</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You’ll have to pay a fee for the licence.</p>\n\n<p>The <a href=\"/taxi-driver-licence\">driver licence</a>, <a href=\"/taxi-vehicle-licence\">vehicle licence</a> and operator licence all need to be issued by the same authority.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"if-your-licence-application-is-refused\">If your licence application is refused</h2>\n\n<p>The licensing authority can refuse your application if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>they’re not satisfied you meet their criteria of a ‘fit and proper person’</li>\n  <li>you do not accept the conditions the authority sets</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If you disagree with their final decision, you can appeal to the magistrates’ court. You might need <a href=\"/find-legal-advice/find-legal-adviser\">legal advice</a>.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"renew-your-licence\">Renew your licence</h2>\n\n<p>Ask the licensing authority how to renew your operator licence.</p>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Warning\" class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You need to renew your licence before it expires or you will not be able to operate a PHV business.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>When you renew your licence, you need to <a href=\"/guidance/complete-a-tax-check-for-a-taxi-private-hire-or-scrap-metal-licence\">complete a tax check</a> telling HM Revenue and Customs (<abbr title=\"HM Revenue and Customs\">HMRC</abbr>) how you pay tax on your earnings.</p>\n\n",
